# Reports Directory Structure.

This folder contains all project-related reports generated during the development, testing, deployment, and completion phases of the **Secure OTA Firmware Update and Code Signing Infrastructure** project.

## File Structure

```text
reports/
├── README.md
├── weekly_progress_report.md
├── integration_test_report.md
├── test_summary_report.md
├── security_assessment_report.md
├── deployment_report.md
├── project_completion_report.md
└── final_project_report.md
```

## Report Descriptions

| File                              | Purpose                                                                                                                  |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **weekly_progress_report.md**     | Records weekly activities, completed tasks, challenges, and achievements throughout the project.                         |
| **integration_test_report.md**    | Documents integration testing results for different modules and components.                                              |
| **test_summary_report.md**        | Provides an overall summary of executed test cases and their outcomes.                                                   |
| **security_assessment_report.md** | Contains findings from security evaluations, vulnerability analysis, and mitigation measures.                            |
| **deployment_report.md**          | Describes deployment procedures, environment setup, and deployment status.                                               |
| **project_completion_report.md**  | Summarizes project milestones, deliverables, and overall accomplishments.                                                |
| **final_project_report.md**       | Serves as the comprehensive report containing architecture, implementation, testing, security analysis, and conclusions. |

## Purpose

These reports ensure:

- Proper project documentation.
- Traceability of development and testing activities.
- Security and quality assurance records.
- Deployment and completion tracking.
- Final project documentation for review and submission.

